<TITLE> Bush calls Hasina </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 10 (bdnews24.com)  US president George W Bush greeted Bangladesh's new prime minister Sheikh Hasina by telephone on Saturday evening, congratulating the country for electing a secular government. The US president congratulated the Awami League president on her landslide victory in the Dec 29 election in his phone call at around 6:40pm (BdST), said a PID statement. It is notable that Bangladeshis voted to establish a non-communal democracy, Bush was quoted to have said. Terming terrorism one of the worst problem in South Asia, the US president stressed the need for effective joint initiatives in order to fight terrorism in the region. Hasina thanked Bush for his call on behalf of the Bangladesh government, people and her party. The two-time premier also thanked the US for its support of the election. The US as well as other countries deserve thanks for their support and assistance for holding a free, fair and neutral election, she was quoted to say. Seeking the US's assistance in fighting poverty, she reiterated her stance that poverty is the main enemy of the country. The two exchanged warm greetings during the conversation, said the PID statement. bd
